<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="243" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,684,1255,1666]" lastBlockId="34.[714,1247,1191,1410]" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">
Ce groupe a une large répartition mondiale et accuse des variations de forme et de coloration intéressantes. Plusieurs espèces ont été décrites: nous citerons 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boas, 1886)" baseAuthorityName="Boas" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[331,679,1384,1410]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Diacria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[331,502,1384,1409]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">Diacria major</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BOAS J. E. V." box="[524,670,1384,1410]" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 231" refId="ref25629" refString="BOAS J. E. V. 1886. - Spolia atlantica. Bidrag til Pteropodernes. Morphologi og systematik samt til kunds kaben om deres geografiske udbredelse. Vidensk Selsk. Skr., 6 Raekke, naturvidensk, mathemat. Afd. IV (1): 1 - 231." type="journal article" year="1886">Boas, 1886</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blainville, 1821)" baseAuthorityName="Blainville" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[151,534,1416,1442]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Hyalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trispinosa">
<emphasis box="[151,303,1416,1441]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">D. trispinosa</emphasis>
(Blainville, 1821)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dupont, 1979" authorityName="Dupont" authorityYear="1979" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Diacria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rampali">
<emphasis box="[552,684,1416,1442]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">D. rampali</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DUPONT L." box="[151,319,1447,1474]" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" pagination="37 - 52" refId="ref26039" refString="DUPONT L. 1979. - Note on variation in Diacria Gray, 1847, with descriptions of a species new to science, Diacria rampali nov. spec., and a forma new to science, Diacria trispinosa forma atlantica nov. forma. Malacologia 18: 37 - 52." type="journal article" year="1979">Dupont, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker &amp; Spoel, 1988" authorityName="Bleeker &amp; Spoel" authorityYear="1988" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Diacria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[336,474,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">D. maculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="BLEEKER J. &amp; SPOEL S. &amp; VAN DER" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" pagination="60 - 66" refId="ref25583" refString="BLEEKER J. &amp; SPOEL S. VAN DER 1988. - Diacria piccola and Diacria maculata: two new Pteropod mollusc species from the Atlantic and Pacific oceans. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 101 (1): 60 - 66." type="journal article" year="1988">Bleeker &amp; Spoel, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker &amp; Spoel, 1988" authorityName="Bleeker &amp; Spoel" authorityYear="1988" box="[232,650,1480,1506]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Diacria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="piccola">
<emphasis box="[232,353,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">D. piccola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="BLEEKER J. &amp; SPOEL S. &amp; VAN DER" box="[366,650,1480,1506]" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" pagination="60 - 66" refId="ref25583" refString="BLEEKER J. &amp; SPOEL S. VAN DER 1988. - Diacria piccola and Diacria maculata: two new Pteropod mollusc species from the Atlantic and Pacific oceans. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 101 (1): 60 - 66." type="journal article" year="1988">Bleeker &amp; Spoel, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName authority="Bontes &amp; Spoel, 1998" authorityName="Bontes &amp; Spoel" authorityYear="1998" box="[151,539,1511,1538]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Diacria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rubecula">
<emphasis box="[151,277,1512,1538]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">D. rubecula</emphasis>
Bontes &amp; Spoel, 1998
</taxonomicName>
. Nous décrivons ici deux taxons nouveaux pour la science, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rampal, 2002" authorityName="Rampal" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,265,1576,1602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Diacria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gracilis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[151,265,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">D. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[277,342,1575,1601]" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
et 
<taxonomicName box="[386,684,1576,1602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Hyalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="trispinosa" subSpecies="heterocolorata">
<emphasis box="[386,684,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">D. trispinosa heterocolorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n. ssp., et reprenons la description de cinq espèces basée sur les données biométriques suivantes: longueur totale (L), longueur de téloconque (La), longueur du corps de la téloconque (Lc), longueur de l’épine postérieure en arrière des épines latérales (Lp), largeur (l), hauteur (H). Angle déterminé par les épines latérales et le plan transversal (α) et par les fentes latérales et le plan sagittal (β) (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1166,1384,1410]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="34.[151,162,1034,1051]" captionTargetBox="[218,1229,171,994]" captionTargetId="figure-238@34.[181,813,142,673]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIG. 17. — Diacria major (Boas, 1886) vue dorsale, ventrale et de profil; A, B, Canaries; C, Sargasses; D, Indien sud-occidental. Abréviations: l, largeur; L, longueur totale; La, longueur de la téloconque; Lc, longueur du corps; Lp, longueur de l’épine postérieure;,, angles de l’axe des épines latérales et des fentes latérales, respectivement, par rapport au plan transversal et longitudinal. Échelle: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5394267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5394267/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="243">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
